Holy Fire Ceremony To Mark Orthodox Easter Held In Near-Empty Jerusalem ChurchEnlarge this image toggle caption Ariel Schalit/AP Ariel Schalit/APUpdated at 2:14 p.m.
ETThe coronavirus did not stop the tradition of the Holy Fire on Saturday, the centuries-old ceremony held annually at the tomb of Jesus in Jerusalem the day before Easter on the Eastern Orthodox Christian calendar.
The ceremony was broadcast live to tens of thousands of Orthodox Christian believers around the world.
Clergy from Greek Orthodox, Armenian, Coptic and Syriac churches were represented at the ceremony, with a few Israeli policemen standing guard.
The Greek Orthodox Patriarch in Jerusalem, Theophilos III, did not wear a mask.